### [Psalms Chapter 149](../../../bib/kjv/psa149.htm#001.md)

[Psalms 149:4](../../../bib/kjv/psa149.htm#004.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_004">psa 149:4</span></span>

The Lord - He rejoiceth over them to do them good. Beautify - Heb.
adorn, make them amiable and honourable in the eyes of the world, who
now hate and despise them. The meek - All true Israelites are such.

[Psalms 149:5](../../../bib/kjv/psa149.htm#005.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_005">psa 149:5</span></span>

In glory - For the honour which God putteth upon them. Beds - By night
as well as by day.

[Psalms 149:7](../../../bib/kjv/psa149.htm#007.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_007">psa 149:7</span></span>

Vengeance - For all their cruelties and injuries towards God's people.
This was literally accomplished by David upon the Philistines,
Ammonites, Syrians and other neighbouring nations.

[Psalms 149:9](../../../bib/kjv/psa149.htm#009.md)

<span class="margnote"><span id="an_009">psa 149:9</span></span>

Written - Appointed and declared in the holy scripture.

